== About Handling Transactions

Transaction Management
In order to activate a transactional connection, the transactionalAction has to be set in the component.

If you want a JMS Listener to use a transactional session when dispatching the messages, you should use ALWAYS_BEGIN:
	<jms:listener config-ref="config" destination="${destination}"
transactionalAction="ALWAYS_BEGIN"/>

By default, other components in the flow will not join the transaction created by the listener. In order to execute other operations using the listenerâ€™s transaction, you must declare them either with ALWAYS_JOIN, or JOIN_IF_POSSIBLE:

<INSERT SCREENSHOT OF FLOW AND CONFIGURATIONS>

<flow name="txSubscriberWithPublish" initialState="stopped">

   <jms:listener config-ref="config" destination="${destination}"
transactionalAction="ALWAYS_BEGIN"/>

   <jms:publish config-ref="config" destination="${publishDestination}"
transactionalAction="ALWAYS_JOIN"/>
</flow>






